FIX 1 — HandTracker AbortError
File: frontend/src/components/HandTracker.tsx
Problem: "AbortError: The play() request was interrupted by a new load request"
React Strict Mode mounts twice, causing camera.start() to be called before first play() resolves.
Fix:
- Add isInitialized = useRef(false) at top of component
- Check if (isInitialized.current) return; at start of useEffect, set true immediately
- Wrap camera.start() in promise chain:
  const startPromise = camera.start();
  if (startPromise !== undefined) {
    startPromise.catch((err) => {
      if (err.name === 'AbortError') { isInitialized.current = false; }
    });
  }
- Never call hands.close() or camera.stop() on unmount — let it persist

