Fix: Ensure WebSocket is created exactly ONCE at the App.tsx level only. Pass the ws instance down as props or context. Remove any secondary useWebSocket calls in child components.

FIX 6 — Port conflict crash on restart
File: backend/ws_server.py
The is_port_in_use check exists but the process still crashes with OSError 10048 on fast restart.
Fix: Add SO_REUSEADDR socket option and a 3-second retry loop before giving up:
  for attempt in range(3):
    try:
      async with websockets.serve(handler, "localhost", 8765, reuse_address=True):
        logger.info("[WebSocket] Server ready")
        await asyncio.Future()
      break
    except OSError as e:
      if attempt < 2:
        logger.warning(f"Port busy, retrying in 3s... ({attempt+1}/3)")
        await asyncio.sleep(3)
      else:
        logger.error("Port 8765 unavailable after 3 attempts")
        await asyncio.Future()

